featured_reviews.review_translated_text: Ashraf Ali Thanvi (August 19, 1863 - July 4, 1945) was a Deobandi scholar, social reformer, Islamic researcher and religious figure. "Thanvi" is added to the end of his name as he is a resident of Thanabhan, India. He is known as "Hakimul Ummat" (Spiritual Physician of the Ummah) as thousands of people in the Indian subcontinent and beyond have learned from him the teachings of self-purification and Tasawwuf. Dawat-ul-Haq was founded by him in Majlise, an organization for spreading the knowledge of Sunnah among Muslims. There is his mausoleum and a mosque here.
